Perfect 👍 Let’s automate it so your search.json updates every day without you doing anything.

There are two common ways:

🔹 Option 1: Windows (Task Scheduler)

If you are on Windows:

Open Task Scheduler (search for it in Start menu).

Click Create Task → give it a name like:
Update Website Search JSON

Go to the Triggers tab → Click New → Set:

Begin the task: On a schedule

Daily → Repeat every 1 day

Pick a time (e.g. 2:00 AM).

Go to the Actions tab → Click New:

Action: Start a program

Program/script: python

Add arguments:

C:\Users\Anne\Documents\website\update_search_json.py


(Change the path to where your script is saved.)

Save → Done ✅

Now Windows will run the script every day at 2 AM and regenerate search.json.


or


 Option 1: Windows (Task Scheduler)

Save your Python script as update_search.py.

Open Task Scheduler (press Windows key → search for "Task Scheduler").

Click Create Basic Task → give it a name like Update Search JSON.

Trigger → choose Daily (set the time, e.g. 2 AM).

Action → choose Start a Program.

Program/script: python

Add arguments: C:\path\to\update_search.py

Start in: C:\path\to\your\script\folder

Save → Done ✅

Now, every day at 2 AM, Windows will run your script → crawl your site → upload new search.json.